{
  "text": "(15) The objective of the next section is to show that the results of [CITATION_1] still holds when the state is partially known. In other words, it will be proved that designing a controller on (14) (u(t) = f (xp)) leads to better disturbance attenuation than designing a controller on (15) (u = f (Xp)). Similarly, to the full state knowledge case,",
